*=======================LAYOUT=============================*

Commas separating selectors make them optional.
.big-text.orange-text (no commas) not optional, must satisfy all conditions.

Specificity is ranked over order

*==scoping==*

h1.class _ insideclass

Box Model: Padding, div, border, margin.

div: a container for the things you want to move around.


box-sizing: moves all the sizing into one.
(padding is part of the overall sizing of an object. )


Explicit vs fluid sizing:


POSITIONING:

Default position static
	Nothing
		Relative
			Essentially same. Objects positioned relatively to everything on the screen.
		Absolute
			Positioning within the parent.
				Position must be relative. For child to be absolute. Changing size of the child changes the size within the parent.
		Fixed
			Doesn't care about parents, position relative to the browser window.




IMAGE:

Place image within a container.
	height: auto;
	width: 100%

background-size: cover;
	change to 100% width.
		background-position: center center;
background-size: contain;
background-repeat: no-repeat;




MULTI-COLUMN LAYOUTS

percentage width is width of the parent.

Display: inline;
	Display: none;
Float
	float: left;
	height: 100vw;
	width: column width'; (33.3% 1/3 columns)

	image float - text wrap

positioning

